OL,3,CThe challenges of monitoring climate
OL,4,Cchange in the Arctic Circle
OL,6,FThe experiment is then repeated over
OL,7,Fand over in slowly increasing
OL,8,Ftemperatures to see how the warmth
OL,9,Faffects their stamina.
OL,11,F"So what I expect, and what my
OL,12,Fcolleagues expect, is that when the
OL,13,Fwater gets warmer, they will have a
OL,14,Frougher time maintaining their
OL,15,Ffitness. It will cost them more energy
OL,16,Fto do their basic living," Max
OL,17,Fexplains.
OL,19,FThe fish may be small but they're a
OL,20,Fvital part of the food chain. A so-
OL,21,Fcalled 'keystone species'.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
