OL,3,CThe challenges of monitoring climate
OL,4,Cchange in the Arctic Circle
OL,6,F"I fear that the water will heat up
OL,7,Ftoo soon, too quick," Max says. "And
OL,8,Ftoo much for them to fulfil their
OL,9,Fbasic needs, and the animals that are
OL,10,Fdependent on them - like the polar
OL,11,Fbears and the narwhals."
OL,13,FIt all sounds rather depressing but
OL,14,FMax believes there is hope. Her
OL,15,Fexperiment suggests the fish can swim
OL,16,Fat slightly warmer temperatures, but
OL,17,Fshe doesn't yet know how much heat
OL,18,Fthey can tolerate.
